♫ Infecting sorrows with smiles ♫

411
00:28:21,370 --> 00:28:26,340
♫ Getting used to what you like,
trying to be brave ♫

412
00:28:26,430 --> 00:28:32,460
♫ Liking becomes natural
and turns into a habit ♫

413
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:37,180
By the way,

414
00:29:38,730 --> 00:29:40,270
I prepared some pills for you.

415
00:29:40,610 --> 00:29:42,370
Take one tablet
when you're having insomnia.

416
00:29:42,460 --> 00:29:43,810
Don't overdose.

417
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:45,230
Every medicine has its side effects.

418
00:29:47,650 --> 00:29:48,530
What's wrong?

419
00:29:49,890 --> 00:29:51,240
Something is wrong with the medicine.

420
00:29:58,500 --> 00:30:01,720
I'll leave Er Miao with you. Let's go.

421
00:30:17,660 --> 00:30:19,120
Custard steamed bun will be ready soon.

422
00:30:20,130 --> 00:30:22,550
Did you cook those dishes?

423
00:30:22,940 --> 00:30:25,070
No, they're cooked by Ms Snail.

424
00:30:27,610 --> 00:30:29,270
What a lame joke.

425
00:30:30,220 --> 00:30:31,400
I love cooking.

426
00:30:31,770 --> 00:30:32,480
Why?

427
00:30:32,570 --> 00:30:34,000
Human heart is located above the stomach.

428
00:30:34,090 --> 00:30:36,160
The way to a man's heart
is through his stomach.

429
00:30:36,970 --> 00:30:38,310
Is it scientifically proven?

430
00:30:38,460 --> 00:30:40,130
Please trust the professional judgment

431
00:30:40,220 --> 00:30:41,350
of a cardiac surgeon.

432
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:43,150
So much for professional judgment.

433
00:30:43,370 --> 00:30:44,550
Have some soup.

434
00:30:54,660 --> 00:30:56,030
[Have you taken the pills I gave you?]

435
00:30:56,690 --> 00:30:57,570
[I took one.]

436
00:30:58,620 --> 00:30:59,500
[You...]

437
00:31:00,210 --> 00:31:01,800
[Did you notice anything?]

438
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:03,440
[What is it?]

439
00:31:06,450 --> 00:31:07,960
You're indeed a straight guy.

440
00:31:10,090 --> 00:31:10,970
Nothing.

441
00:31:15,610 --> 00:31:17,000
How many days will you stay?

442
00:31:17,570 --> 00:31:18,450
I'm going back to
the military camp tomorrow.

443
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:22,170
All your comrades are back, right?

444
00:31:22,260 --> 00:31:23,190
Yes, they're back.

445
00:31:25,580 --> 00:31:26,460
Good to hear that.

446
00:31:29,770 --> 00:31:31,280
I was under the impression

447
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:33,950
doctors take life and death lightly.

448
00:31:36,930 --> 00:31:38,320
I don't know about others

449
00:31:38,610 --> 00:31:39,490
but I...

450
00:31:40,180 --> 00:31:42,080
I don't have the talent
to take it lightly.

451
00:31:44,500 --> 00:31:46,360
When I was undergoing rotation
at the Obstetrics Department,

452
00:31:47,370 --> 00:31:48,760
there was an old pregnant woman.

453
00:31:49,490 --> 00:31:51,080
She couldn't give birth to the baby.

454
00:31:52,940 --> 00:31:54,310
She held my hand and said,

455
00:31:55,770 --> 00:31:58,240
"Doctor, it's too painful."

456
00:31:58,900 --> 00:32:00,070
"I don't want to do it anymore."

457
00:32:02,540 --> 00:32:03,710
Two minutes later,

458
00:32:05,690 --> 00:32:07,670
she passed away due to
amniotic fluid embolism.

459
00:32:09,410 --> 00:32:10,510
Her husband

460
00:32:11,290 --> 00:32:13,200
while carrying the newborn

461
00:32:13,450 --> 00:32:14,760
burst into loud sobs.

462
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:17,280
I never knew

463
00:32:18,450 --> 00:32:20,600
a man could cry for so long.

464
00:32:24,220 --> 00:32:25,320
That was the first time

465
00:32:26,540 --> 00:32:28,520
I witnessed the death of a patient.

466
00:32:30,700 --> 00:32:31,730
Until now, I still vividly remember

467
00:32:31,820 --> 00:32:33,710
the moment she lied
on the operating table.

468
00:32:35,050 --> 00:32:35,810
I always feel that a hand

469
00:32:35,900 --> 00:32:37,590
is holding me down.

470
00:32:40,530 --> 00:32:41,600
No matter how difficult it is,

471
00:32:42,330 --> 00:32:44,150
she motivates me to run forward.

472
00:32:49,890 --> 00:32:50,770
[I'm sorry.]

473
00:33:20,020 --> 00:33:22,880
Five years ago, I went to Yunnan
for residency training.

474
00:33:25,010 --> 00:33:26,230
I received a phone call from home

475
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:27,750
informing me that
my grandma was terminally ill.

476
00:33:29,410 --> 00:33:31,880
I applied for leave and rushed home.

477
00:33:33,690 --> 00:33:35,030
When I reached home,

478
00:33:36,130 --> 00:33:37,520
my grandma was already unable to talk.

479
00:33:38,730 --> 00:33:39,760
However, when she saw me,

480
00:33:39,850 --> 00:33:41,880
she got agitated. She cried non-stop.

481
00:33:44,010 --> 00:33:44,890
I don't think I would ever

482
00:33:44,980 --> 00:33:46,230
understand how she felt.

483
00:33:47,770 --> 00:33:49,400
I didn't know what to do.

484
00:33:49,620 --> 00:33:51,110
I didn't know what I could do.

485
00:33:52,580 --> 00:33:53,710
I sat at the bedside.

486
00:33:55,050 --> 00:33:56,000
I held her hand

487
00:33:57,770 --> 00:33:58,870
and sang her a song.

488
00:34:00,570 --> 00:34:02,040
So, my grandma passed away

489
00:34:03,340 --> 00:34:05,150
as I sang.

490
00:34:08,690 --> 00:34:09,650
Then, I could feel the warmth of her palm

491
00:34:09,740 --> 00:34:11,040
slowly disappearing.

492
00:34:11,300 --> 00:34:12,630
In the end, it turned completely cold.

493
00:34:14,260 --> 00:34:15,510
But at that moment,

494
00:34:16,490 --> 00:34:17,510
I was really calm.

495
00:34:23,649 --> 00:34:24,530
Yes.

496
00:34:25,770 --> 00:34:26,750
Calm.

497
00:34:35,089 --> 00:34:35,410
[Why are we talking about this]

498
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:37,120
[all of a sudden?]

499
00:34:38,050 --> 00:34:39,000
You started it first.

500
00:34:40,570 --> 00:34:41,450
However,

501
00:34:41,810 --> 00:34:43,439
it's okay to talk about it.

502
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:45,550
Military officers and doctors

503
00:34:45,820 --> 00:34:47,200
are two occupations

504
00:34:47,290 --> 00:34:48,480
that are close to death.

505
00:34:49,609 --> 00:34:51,000
We understand death.

506
00:34:51,140 --> 00:34:53,000
That's why we cherish the moment.

507
00:34:54,129 --> 00:34:55,470
When we're alive,

508
00:34:56,010 --> 00:34:57,720
we won't miss out on
any wonderful moments.

509
00:34:58,530 --> 00:34:59,410
Am I right?

510
00:35:02,250 --> 00:35:03,390
You are afraid of missing out.

511
00:35:16,250 --> 00:35:17,150
Do you want some?

512
00:35:20,010 --> 00:35:22,190
Does it go well with Chinese cuisine?

513
00:35:22,380 --> 00:35:23,310
I like it.

514
00:35:25,370 --> 00:35:26,680
We deserve to take a well-earned break.

515
00:35:26,900 --> 00:35:28,230
We can have some liquor.

516
00:35:31,180 --> 00:35:32,110
Just a sip.

517
00:35:46,580 --> 00:35:47,710
Bourbon Whiskey.

518
00:35:48,290 --> 00:35:49,390
It's Matthew's favourite drink.

519
00:35:50,490 --> 00:35:51,370
Who is that?

520
00:35:52,810 --> 00:35:54,990
He's a detective
in Lawrence Block's novel.

521
00:36:07,940 --> 00:36:08,990
When I was in high school,

522
00:36:09,340 --> 00:36:11,120
a new student joined our class.

523
00:36:11,490 --> 00:36:12,830
He sat beside me.

524
00:36:13,540 --> 00:36:14,840
Under his influence,

525
00:36:15,420 --> 00:36:17,040
I started reading detective novels.

526
00:36:18,180 --> 00:36:19,110
He said

527
00:36:19,410 --> 00:36:21,560
he wanted to be a detective novelist.

528
00:36:23,290 --> 00:36:24,320
However,

529
00:36:24,690 --> 00:36:26,470
due to the harsh reality,

530
00:36:26,690 --> 00:36:28,630
he didn't realise his dream.

531
00:36:29,410 --> 00:36:32,070
He said he wanted to be
a National Defence Student

532
00:36:32,530 --> 00:36:34,320
and contribute to society
by joining the special forces.

533
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:36,690
Back then,

534
00:36:36,780 --> 00:36:38,400
no matter what he said or what he did,

535
00:36:39,210 --> 00:36:41,070
I always thought that he was right.

536
00:36:44,090 --> 00:36:45,440
However, one day,

537
00:36:45,660 --> 00:36:47,270
he disappeared from school.

538
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:50,080
I couldn't find him anywhere.

539
00:36:50,690 --> 00:36:52,230
I didn't know where to find him.

540
00:36:53,700 --> 00:36:55,080
I couldn't do anything besides reading

541
00:36:55,170 --> 00:36:57,150
the detective novels he got me one by one.

542
00:36:58,690 --> 00:37:00,350
Then, I bought more novels from
the book store.

543
00:37:01,620 --> 00:37:02,790
I even hoped that

544
00:37:03,380 --> 00:37:04,090
one day,

545
00:37:04,180 --> 00:37:06,510
in one of the detective novels,

546
00:37:06,820 --> 00:37:11,000
I could see his name, Zhuo Ran.

547
00:37:17,290 --> 00:37:20,000
He is now neither a novelist
nor a military officer.

548
00:37:21,170 --> 00:37:23,230
He set up a 3D printing company.

549
00:37:23,860 --> 00:37:24,960
He's now a business owner.

550
00:37:26,210 --> 00:37:27,310
I have retained a habit of his

551
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:29,600
in my own life.

552
00:37:31,690 --> 00:37:33,120
However, I was already 18

553
00:37:33,610 --> 00:37:34,910
and our high school memories

554
00:37:36,130 --> 00:37:37,430
were gone for good.

555
00:37:41,930 --> 00:37:43,030
